==================================================
LVCSR             大词汇量连续语音识别（Large vocabulary continuous speech recognition）
partial order	  偏序关系








Our clustering algorithm has two stages. We first merge only equivalence classes corresponding to instances of the same word (intra-word clustering), and
then start grouping together heterogeneous equivalence classes (inter-word clustering), based on the phonetic similarity of the word components.



Each equivalence class corresponds to one “position” in the alignment
and the members of a class are those word hypotheses that are “aligned to each other“

We initialize the link equivalence such that each initial class consists of all the links with the same starting and ending times and the same word label

1 The purpose of this step is to group together all the links corresponding to same word instance
	SIM(E 1 , E 2 ) =
　	max overlap(e 1 , e 2 ) · p(e 1 ) · p(e 2 )

2 this step we group together equivalence classes corresponding to different words. Candidates for merging are any two classes that are not in relation
















